Goal
- Fix the input lag in the search box of the React app caused by rendering performance issues with a list of around 500 items, without changing the UI or breaking the existing filtering functionality.

Context
- Stack: React with TypeScript.
- Relevant files: search box component, list rendering component(s).
- Existing patterns: current filtering logic and UI must remain unchanged.

Constraints
- Preserve the current UI design exactly.
- Do not break or alter the filtering behavior.
- Avoid introducing new dependencies.
- Maintain TypeScript typing and code style.
- Limit changes to performance optimizations related to rendering and state management.

Output format
- Use headings.
- Show unified diffs only.
- Put code changes in fenced blocks.
- Keep explanations concise (under 200 words).
- End with a checklist of tests and edge cases to verify performance improvement and correctness.

Examples
- Use React.memo or equivalent to prevent unnecessary re-renders of list items.
- Implement debouncing or throttling on the search input if appropriate.
- Optimize filtering logic to avoid recomputation on every keystroke.

Success criteria
- Search input no longer lags noticeably during typing.
- Filtering results remain accurate and consistent with current behavior.
- UI appearance is identical before and after the fix.
- No new runtime errors or TypeScript type issues introduced.

Verification
- Verify smooth typing experience in the search box with 500 items.
- Confirm filtering correctness and UI consistency through manual testing.